# Deploy to VPS ‚Äî runbook (TEMPLATE)

> **Copy this to `DEPLOY_TO_VPS.md` and fill in real values.** The real file is
> **gitignored** (it holds your hosts/logins/keys) ‚Äî never commit it. Private SSH
> keys live in `~/.ssh/`, not here. Placeholders below use the repo convention
> (`203.0.113.x`); replace every `<‚Ä¶>` and example value with yours.

How to ship the current `main` to your production VPS(es). Each runs the daemon
as a hardened systemd service from `/opt/orquester` (appdir `/var/lib/orquester`),
behind Caddy on 443; the daemon listens on loopback `127.0.0.1:47831`.

## TL;DR

1. **Push first** ‚Äî the VPSes pull from `origin/main`:
   ```sh
   git push origin main
   ```
2. **Deploy each VPS** (run the one-liners below). They're independent.
3. **Browser smoke test each deployed URL** (mandatory after web/ui changes):
   ```sh
   node scripts/smoke-web.mjs https://example.com
   ```
   Loads the SPA headlessly with clean storage **and** with legacy localStorage
   fixtures (`scripts/smoke-web-fixtures.json`); fails on any uncaught page
   error, console error, or empty `#root`. Catches the "health curl is green but
   the page crashes on users' stale persisted state" class. Runs from your dev
   machine; needs a system Chrome/Chromium (`SMOKE_CHROME=` to override).

## Targets

| Name | Host (IP) | SSH login | Key | Privilege | Domain |
|------|-----------|-----------|-----|-----------|--------|
| **vps-a** | `203.0.113.10` | `root` | `~/.ssh/<key_a>` | runs as root, **no sudo** | `example.com` |
| **vps-b** | `203.0.113.20` | `<user>` | `~/.ssh/<key_b>` | **`sudo` for git/pnpm/chown/systemctl** | `example.net` |

Notes / per-host quirks to record here:
- Whether the host has a `~/.ssh/config` entry (and whether it sets `User`), so you know if you must connect as `<user>@host` explicitly.
- Whether you need `-i ~/.ssh/<key>`, `-o IdentitiesOnly=yes`, and/or `-o StrictHostKeyChecking=accept-new` (e.g. a host key that rotates).
- Whether `/opt/orquester` is root-owned (‚áí a non-root login needs `sudo` for git/pnpm/chown/systemctl, ideally NOPASSWD).

## Deploy ‚Äî a root-login VPS

```sh
ssh -o ConnectTimeout=15 -o StrictHostKeyChecking=accept-new root@203.0.113.10 'set -e
  cd /opt/orquester
  git fetch origin -q && git reset --hard origin/main
  echo "HEAD=$(git rev-parse --short HEAD)"
  CI=1 ELECTRON_SKIP_BINARY_DOWNLOAD=1 pnpm install --frozen-lockfile </dev/null
  ELECTRON_SKIP_BINARY_DOWNLOAD=1 pnpm --filter @orquester/web build </dev/null
  chown -R root:root /opt/orquester
  systemctl restart orquester
  curl -fsS --retry 25 --retry-delay 1 --retry-connrefused http://127.0.0.1:47831/health; echo
  echo "service=$(systemctl is-active orquester)"'
```

## Deploy ‚Äî a sudo-login VPS (non-root user)

```sh
ssh -o ConnectTimeout=15 -o StrictHostKeyChecking=accept-new -o IdentitiesOnly=yes -i ~/.ssh/<key_b> <user>@203.0.113.20 'set -e
  cd /opt/orquester
  sudo git fetch origin -q && sudo git reset --hard origin/main
  echo "HEAD=$(sudo git rev-parse --short HEAD)"
  sudo CI=1 ELECTRON_SKIP_BINARY_DOWNLOAD=1 pnpm install --frozen-lockfile </dev/null
  sudo ELECTRON_SKIP_BINARY_DOWNLOAD=1 pnpm --filter @orquester/web build </dev/null
  sudo chown -R root:root /opt/orquester
  sudo systemctl restart orquester
  curl -fsS --retry 25 --retry-delay 1 --retry-connrefused http://127.0.0.1:47831/health; echo
  echo "service=$(systemctl is-active orquester)"'
```

## What each step does

| Step | Why |
|------|-----|
| `git fetch + reset --hard origin/main` | Tree is root-owned (immutable code); reset to the pushed commit. |
| `CI=1 pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` | Reconciles deps to the lockfile. **`CI=1` is non-negotiable**: it makes pnpm non-interactive, so a *"reinstall modules from scratch? (Y/n)"* prompt (fired when `node_modules` was built by a different pnpm version) **auto-proceeds** instead of wedging the non-TTY deploy. `--frozen-lockfile` installs exactly what's locked and **fails loudly** on lockfile drift; it's a fast no-op when deps are unchanged. |
| `pnpm --filter @orquester/web build` | Rebuilds the **served SPA** (`apps/web/dist`). Only needed when `web`/`ui`/`api` changed ‚Äî harmless to always run. The **daemon** needs no build (tsx runs the new `.ts` after restart). |
| `chown -R root:root /opt/orquester` | Keep code root-owned (avoids git "dubious ownership"; the daemon runs as a different user). |
| `systemctl restart orquester` | Near-instant graceful restart. `KillMode=process` ‚áí the tmux server + all terminal/agent sessions **survive** and the daemon reattaches. |
| health `curl` | Expect `{"ok":true}`. `--retry-connrefused` rides out the ~1‚Äì2 s restart window (a few `connection refused` lines are normal). |

## Gotchas

- **Push before deploying** ‚Äî the VPSes only see what's on `origin/main`.
- **Always run the install with `CI=1`.** Without it, pnpm's interactive *"reinstall modules from scratch? (Y/n)"* prompt blocks on the non-TTY SSH and silently breaks the deploy (it skips installing new deps, then the build fails to resolve them). `CI=1 ‚Ä¶ pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` is safe to run every time ‚Äî a fast no-op when nothing changed.
- **Never pipe the build through `| tail`/`| grep`.** A pipeline's exit status is the *last* command's, so `set -e` won't catch a failed `vite build` ‚Äî the script would march past it and `systemctl restart` into a stale/broken `dist`. Run the build bare (let `set -e` abort), or redirect to a file and check `$?`.
- **Detach pnpm's stdin (`</dev/null`) ‚Äî critical inside a piped `bash -s`.** If you wrap a multi-step deploy as `ssh host 'bash -s' <<'EOF' ‚Ä¶ EOF` (or `sudo bash -s`), a `pnpm install`/`build` in that script **reads the remaining script lines from stdin** (pnpm reads stdin ‚Äî e.g. on its *"ignored build scripts ‚Üí run pnpm approve-builds"* notice), so every step **after** pnpm silently never runs and the deploy looks done while the bundle/Caddy were never touched. The one-liners above already append `</dev/null` to each pnpm command. If you must run a longer combined script, **write it to a file and `bash file`** rather than piping it to `bash -s`. Always confirm a deploy by the **live bundle hash** (`curl -s http://127.0.0.1:47831/ | grep -o 'index-[^.]*\.js'`), not by the SSH output.
- **Daemon-only changes need no build** ‚Äî just `systemctl restart`. Only the SPA needs `pnpm build`.
- **Caddy** only needs a reload if `deploy/Caddyfile` changed (`systemctl reload caddy`).
- **Browser cache:** after a web change, hard-reload the open app (Cmd/Ctrl+Shift+R).
- `47831` is loopback-only; never exposed. Caddy (443) is the public face.

## Troubleshooting

- Logs: `journalctl -u orquester -n 50 --no-pager` (prefix `sudo` for a non-root login).
- Service state: `systemctl status orquester`.
- Rolled back? `git reset --hard <good-sha>` then rebuild + restart.
- Rotate the password: edit `/etc/orquester/daemon.env` (`ORQUESTER_HTTP_PASSWORD`), `systemctl restart orquester` (re-hashes into `daemon.json`).
